            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Color",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>1.] The first stone represents memories and experiences from the past.<br/><br/>2.] The center stone represents the present moment and the bond shared today.<br/><br/>3.] The third stone symbolizes the future and everything still to come.<br/><br/>Because of this meaning, trilogy rings are often chosen for engagements, anniversaries, or major life milestones.</p><p>Rings like the<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/products/three-stone-oval-anniversary-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Three-Stone Oval Anniversary Ring\"> Three-Stone Oval Anniversary Ring</a> beautifully capture this idea, making them a thoughtful gift for couples celebrating years together. </p>",
            "custom_id": "color",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_ry4cQt": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Color",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/color.jpg",
            "text": "<p>In a clear, colorless diamond, light passes through effortlessly, enhancing its brilliance. However, as color increases, light has a harder time passing through, often making the diamond appear darker or less vibrant.</p><p>Most diamonds fall within a spectrum ranging from completely colorless to those with a visible yellow or brown tint. The rarest and most expensive diamonds are graded <em>D, E, or F, </em>indicating they are colorless. </p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "marquise-bezel-diamond-stud-earrings",
              "0-50-ct-pear-solitaire-cascade-hoops-earrings"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>This grading scale runs down to <em>Z</em>, where the presence of color becomes more noticeable. Diamonds that display color beyond <em>Z</em>, or appear in shades like pink, blue, or orange, are classified as <em>Fancy Colored Diamonds</em>.</p><p>While Mined Diamonds can be found across this entire scale, Lab Grown Diamonds are typically graded <em>J (near colorless)</em> or better. This is because, in the controlled environment of a Lab, the mineral contamination that cause color are far less likely to occur, resulting in clearer stones by default.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Clarity",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Clarity</h2><p>Clarity measures the purity of a diamond. During a diamond’s formation, it’s common for tiny impurities to become trapped either inside the diamond or on its surface.</p>",
            "custom_id": "clarity",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_BiE3eV": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Clarity",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Clarity.webp",
            "text": "<p>Clarity characteristics are divided into two types: <em>Inclusions</em> (internal features) and <em>Blemishes</em> (external marks). Even when these are too small to be seen without magnification, they can still affect how light moves through the diamond. As a result, their size, shape, and position play an important role in diamond grading. Importantly, <em>Inclusions</em> do not affect the structural stability of a diamond.</p><p>There are 11 clarity grades, ranging from <em>FL</em> (flawless internally and externally) to <em>I</em> (with significant inclusions and blemishes).</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "0-20-cts-dewdrop-diamond-ring",
              "0-25-cts-classic-solitaire-diamond-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qwTzXx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Make sure to check a diamond’s certificate before you make a purchase, as a diamond with fewer imperfections will come at a higher asking price. Imperfections also give each diamond its own unique character, and to many, these add to its beauty.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mEE3FU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Carat",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Carat</h2><p>Carat is a measurement of weight, derived from the word \"carob\"; in ancient times, carob seeds were used as a reference for diamond weight.</p>",
            "custom_id": "carat",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_XgNzg9": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Carat",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/carat.jpg",
            "text": "<p>One carat weighs 1/5 of a gram and is divided into 100 points, so a diamond weighing 1.05 ct. is referred to as \"one carat and five points\". Today, precise measurements are taken to the hundredth decimal place to ensure complete accuracy.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "0-44ct-half-eternity-pave-diamond-band",
              "0-4ct-emerald-round-toi-et-moi-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Diamond prices rise exponentially with carat weight. So, a 2-carat diamond of a given quality is always worth more than two 1-carat diamonds of the same quality. However, the carat weight by itself does not determine a diamond’s value. Two diamonds of equal carat weight may have very different values based on the other factors: all the 4Cs have an influence on each other in diamond grading.</p><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Lab Grown Diamonds have opened a world of possibilities, offering the same brilliance, strength and beauty as mined diamonds but at a far more accessible price. Grown under conditions that replicate the earth’s natural processes, they share the exact same physical and chemical properties as their mined counterparts, differing only in their origin.</p><p>Like Mined Diamonds, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry's</a> Lab Grown Diamonds are graded by the 4Cs, giving you a trusted framework to understand a diamond's qualities. However, the 4Cs are simply a guide, not a rulebook. No two diamonds are alike, true beauty lies in what you personally connect with and that’s what makes it truly special.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
      },
